Reinvesting in America
Community Involvement











Blood  Drives





                          Several of our locations hold on-site blood drives  throughout the year to allow employees an opportunity to participate in this  important cause. The combined total of the blood drives results in more than  500 units and each blood donation helps three patients.



SEAL Legacy Foundation
                            NCI has been a presenting sponsor for the SEAL Legacy Foundation Gala   and Golf Classic Tournament since 2011, supporting the mission to raise   funds for scholarships and financial needs of U.S Navy SEALs and their   families. As a longtime supporter of the U.S. military and the SEALs in   particular Norm Chambers, NCI’s CEO and Chairman was honored in July   2014 with the inaugural SEAL Legacy Foundation Founders Award in   recognition of NCI’s ongoing advocacy for the organization since its   inception. 



Supporting Our Veterans





                            NCI sponsors ConocoPhillip's annual Sporting Clays Tournament which   raises money for veterans. Over the past six years, the tournament has   raised over $800,000 for veteran charities and more than 550 registrants   participate in the fundraiser annually. In addition to monetary   sponsorship, NCI's employees volunteer as part of the 300 plus   volunteers that help at the event. It's just one more way NCI supports   our Veterans. 



Breast  Cancer Awareness





                            NCI has participated in the Susan G. Komen Breast  Cancer Awareness program for many years. Employees who make a minimum $5 donation receive a pink ribbon pin in October, and are comforted  knowing they were able to support a worthy cause.



Caring  is Sharing Christmas Gift Drive






                            Employees volunteer to sponsor children and  adults in need by furnishing gifts at Christmas. The gifts include clothing items and a toy or item that the recipient has requested. Gifts are collected and distributed to the children and adults in  mid-December.  










 

























