NCS - Market Data & News
NCS - Stock Valuation Report
 Trade 

NCI Building Systems Inc. New (NCS) traded on unusually high volume on Jul. 26, as the stock 
gained 1.41% to close at $17.95. On the day, NCI Building Systems Inc. New saw 974,060 shares trade hands on 4,757 trades. 
Considering that the stock averages only a daily volume of 414,148 shares a day over the last month, this represents a pretty significant bump in volume over the norm.

Generally speaking, when a stock experiences a sudden spike in trading volume, it may be seen as a bullish signal for investors. An increase in volume means more market awareness for the 
company, potentially setting up a more meaningful move in stock price. The added volume also provides a level of support and stability for price advances.

The stock has traded between $18.10 and $13.80 over the last 52-weeks, its 50-day SMA is now $17.11, and its 200-day SMA $16.34. NCI Building Systems Inc. New 
has a P/B ratio of 4.2. It also has a P/E ratio of 20.6.  


NCI Building Systems Inc is an integrated manufacturer and marketer of metal products for the nonresidential construction industry. The Company's products are used in repair, retrofit and new construction activities, in North America.

Headquartered in Houston, TX, NCI Building Systems Inc. New has 5,500 employees and is currently under the leadership of CEO Norman C. Chambers.


