NCI Building Systems, Inc. New (NYSE:NCS) Experiences Lighter than Usual Trading Volume - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
NCI Building Systems, Inc. New (NYSE:NCS) Experiences Lighter than Usual Trading Volume
July 25, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





NCI Building Systems, Inc. New shares had a trading volume of 19K by the end of trading on Tuesday.  Overall, volume was down 94.12% under the stocks normal daily volume. 
 Here are a few additional firms who have increased or decreased their stake in (NCS).   Seabridge Investment Advisors LLC divested its investment by selling 2,690 shares a decrease of 1.4% as of 06/30/2017. Seabridge Investment Advisors LLC owns 191,430 shares valued at $3,197,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 4.0%. Skylands Capital, LLC reduced its stake by shedding 9,600 shares a decrease of 4.8% from 03/31/2017 to 06/30/2017. Skylands Capital, LLC now controls 189,000 shares with a value of $3,156,000. The value of the position overall is down by 7.3%.
 As of the end of the quarter Peregrine Capital Management LLC had disposed of 3,450 shares trimming its position 0.3%. The value in dollars went from $22,096,000 to $22,511,000 increasing 1.9% quarter over quarter. Legato Capital Management LLC grew its holdings by buying 31,382 shares an increase of 1,236.0%. Legato Capital Management LLC controls 33,921 shares worth $566,000. The total value of its holdings increased 1,186.4%.
  On May 19 the company was downgraded to “Neutral” from “Buy” in a report issued by DA Davidson. March 10 investment analysts at Credit Suisse held the stock rating at “Outperform” and raised the price target  to $14.00 from $13.00.
 On September 4 BB&T Capital maintained a company rating of “Buy” but lowered the price target from $20.00 to $17.00. September 4 investment analysts at RBC Capital held the company rating at “Sector Perform” but lowered the price expectation from $17.00 to $13.00.





 On September 3 UBS left the company rating at “Buy” but moved down the price target  to $17.00 from $20.00. On September 1 Stephens & Co. kept the stock rating at “Overweight” and lowered the price expectation  to $13.00 from $18.00.
 In the market the company is trading up by 0.85% since yesterday’s close of $17.55.  Shares of the company are trading at $17.70 a tad above the 50 day moving average which is $17.21 and barely above the 200 day moving average of $16.63.  The 50 day moving average was up $0.52 and the 200 day average went up by +6.597%. 
 The P/E ratio is currently 20.683 and the market cap is 1.26B.  In the last earnings report the EPS was $0.86 and is estimated to be $1.00 for the current year with 70,899,000 shares presently outstanding.  Analysts expect next quarter’s EPS will be $0.47 and the next full year EPS is anticipated to be $1.24. 
 NCI Building Systems, Inc., launched on December 23, 1991, is a manufacturer and marketer of metal products in North America. The Business’s operating segments include Engineered building systems, Metal components and Metal coil coating. The Engineered building systems segment is involved in the manufacturing of main frames and long bay systems, and engineering and drafting. The Metal components segment’s products include metal roof and wall panels, doors, metal partitions, metal trim, insulated metal panel (IMP) products and other related accessories. The Company manufactures and distributes a range of metal products for the non-residential construction market. It operates in the United States, Mexico, Canada and China. The Company provides metal coil coating services, and designs, engineers, manufactures and markets metal components and engineered building systems. It also provides metal coil coating services for commercial and construction applications, servicing both internal and external customers..






