Overview
Metal Coil Coating
Metal Components
Metal Building Systems
Our Brands/Companies











Uses: Custom-designed building systems are used for manufacturing facilities, energy-related facilities, mining, warehouses, office buildings, showrooms, retail shopping centers, banks, schools, places of worship, distribution centers, government buildings, community centers, etc.   
Products: We are one of the three largest producers of metal building systems in the United States, accounting for approximately 24% market share. We design, manufacture and sell low-rise (up to five stories) metal buildings for nonresidential markets.  

Process: We design, engineer and fabricate our buildings to meet the customer's requirements and the structural provisions of the specified building code. We make the different parts of the building at our various manufacturing facilities within our accredited quality program guidelines. We ship these components to the job site for assembly with usually no field welding required. 
Customers: We have customers in all the nonresidential sectors, including commercial, industrial, agricultural, governmental and institutional. We market our building systems through an in-house sales force to an authorized builder network of over 3,300 builders. We also sell building systems to general contractors and directly to end users as well as to private-label companies, both in the U.S. and around 
the world. 
Manufacturing facilities:  We have manufacturing facilities strategically located throughout North America. (click here to see map)
 

